AB  - A number of techniques have recently appeared in the literature utilizing instantaneous nonlinear transformations of stochastic processes. As in economics most variables appear to be nonstationary, it is interesting to investigate the temporal properties of nonlinear transformations of these processes. Using a unified approach based on Hermite polynomials, this paper provides some insight for polynomial, exponential, periodic, and neural-network transformations of first-order integrated processes.
